The Kaduna State government, yesterday, extended the 24-hour curfew imposed on Thursday to two chiefdoms in Kauru and Zangon Kataf local government areas. The state’s commissioner, Ministry of Internal Security and Home Affairs, Samuel Aruwan, while giving an update on the security situation in the affected areas, said the security agencies are working to contain the situation which started as a clash over farmland. The short statement said, “Security agencies are working to contain the situation that started as a clash over a farmland. Extending the curfew is part of the necessary steps to manage the tensions and restore calm,” Aruwan updated.